    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.60d Finnish Vessels/150.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Finnish Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Järnefelt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-01">February 1,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform Your Excellency
                    that on January 30, 1935, a complete record in two volumes,<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d159fn10">Not printed.</note> regarding the claims for the detention
                    of 13 Finnish sailing vessels for various periods during 1918, prepared by Mr.
                    John G. Poore, Attorney at Law, has been handed to the Legal Adviser of the
                    Department of State, Mr. Hackworth.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eero Järnefelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
